articles.description: Quinton Rose scored 16 of his 20 points in the second half when Temple pulled away from USF for its fifth-straight win 73-55 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Rose scores 20, Temple pulls away from USF 73-55

articles.description: Jalan McCloud had 20 points on 7-of-13 shooting and Devontavius Payne scored 11 points, including three 3-pointers, to help East Tennessee State beat VMI 70-56 on Saturday.
articles.headline: ETSU beats VMI, ties program record with 16th straight win

articles.description: Baylor's Mark Vital leaps up and swats away a 3-point attempt by Malik Newman in the closing seconds of the first half.
articles.headline: Vital denies Newman's corner 3 before first-half buzzer

images.caption: Baylor's Mark Vital leaps up and swats away a 3-point attempt by Malik Newman in the closing seconds of the first half.
images.name: Vital denies Newman's corner 3 before first-half buzzer

articles.description: Kendall Smith and Cameron McGriff each scored 20 points and Oklahoma State beat another ranked team on the road, topping No. 19 West Virginia 88-85 Saturday.
articles.headline: Oklahoma State tops struggling No. 19 West Virginia 88-85

images.caption: Each of Oklahoma State's starters score in double figures in an 88-85 upset over West Virginia.
images.name: Oklahoma State rallies past WVU

articles.description: Shamorie Ponds continued his incredible play by scoring 44 points and resurgent St. John's, coming off consecutive victories over top-five teams, defeated Marquette 86-78 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Ponds scores 44 in St. John's third straight victory, 86-78

images.caption: Shamorie Ponds score a career-high 44 points as St. John's wins its third straight game with an 86-78 victory over Marquette.
images.name: Ponds scores 44 in St. John's win over Marquette
